## Official Motion Studio MCP (motion.dev)

The official Motion Studio MCP from motion.dev can be installed with the following configuration:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "motion": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "https://api.motion.dev/registry.tgz?package=motion-studio-mcp&version=latest"]
    }
  }
}
```

To enable Motion+ features like the codex and curve visualisation, you need to install with your personal access token:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "motion": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "https://api.motion.dev/registry.tgz?package=motion-studio-mcp&version=latest"],
      "env": {
        "TOKEN": "<YOUR_TOKEN>"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Motion Studio provides visual editing tools via the Motion Studio extension, and AI editing tools via the Motion Studio MCP. Currently, both must be installed separately.(no content)Motion Studio is also compatible with VS Code, Google Antigravity and more.(no content)The Motion Studio MCP provides the latest Motion documentation to your AI editor via Resources. Additionally, Motion+ users can access an additional MCP server to access docs for Motion+ APIs.

## Third-Party Motion.dev MCP Servers

### Abhishekrajpurohit/motion-dev-mcp
A MCP server providing offline Motion.dev documentation access and intelligent animation code generation for React, JavaScript, and Vue. Features multi-framework support, advanced search capabilities, and production-quality component generation through AI.(no content)Installation requires cloning the repository, running `npm install`, `npm run build`, and `npm run rebuild` to initialize the documentation database.

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "motion-dev": {
      "command": "node",
      "args": ["./dist/index.js"],
      "cwd": "$HOME/motion-dev-mcp"
    }
  }
}
```

The server includes 26 pages of documentation (React: 7, JavaScript: 13, Vue: 6), 63 enhanced component definitions, and 351 working code examples across all frameworks.


